Our study utilized resting-state fMRI data from the publicly available Alzheimer's Disease Neuroimaging Initiative (ADNI2) database. 
The final cohort comprised 507 subjects: 135 Normal Controls (NC, age: 65-95), 98 patients with Alzheimer's Disease (AD, age: 56-89), 168 patients with Early Mild Cognitive Impairment (EMCI, age: 56-90) and 106 patients with Late Mild Cognitive Impairment (LMCI, age: 57-86).
